# Code Structure

## Universal thresholds

| Rule | Warn | Hard limit |
|------|------|------------|
| File length | >300 lines | >500 lines |
| Function/method | >40 lines | >75 lines |
| Class/component file | >200 lines | — |
| Nesting depth | >3 levels | — |
| Parameters | >4 | group into object |
| Single responsibility | one primary concern per file | — |

Exclude: generated files, `package-lock.json`, `globals.css` (styles).

## TypeScript / React (this project)

- No `any` — use `unknown` and narrow, or define types
- Named exports for lib and shared components; default export only for Next `page.tsx` / `layout.tsx`
- One primary component per file; private sub-components co-located OK
- Custom hooks >60 lines → split
- No business logic in components — access checks live in `src/lib/documents.ts`; validation in `src/lib/validation.ts`
- No direct `prisma` in components — use API routes or server pages
- Client `fetch` to `/api/*` only; no external API URLs in components

## Next.js API routes (this project)

- Handlers: auth → validate (Zod) → lib/prisma → `NextResponse.json`
- Return `{ error: string }` with correct status; catch blocks return 500 JSON, never throw to client
- Route params: `params: Promise<{ id: string }>` — always `await params`
- Keep handlers readable; extract repeated logic to `src/lib/**`

## Enforcement

Before marking any task complete, check every touched file against thresholds. Fix or flag violations with file + line range.

